<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,1981,2006]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1436,151,467]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="411" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,282,1981,2006]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
The male 
<typeStatus box="[415,516,1981,2006]" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">holotype</typeStatus>
, and up to now the only recorded specimen, is inaccessible (
<collectionCode box="[1245,1304,1982,2006]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/804h-arc5" name="Indian Forest Research Institute" pageId="9" pageNumber="410">IFRI</collectionCode>
). However, Beeson provided a clear description of the species, and in addition, we have examined a drawing of the elytral declivity (
<collectionCode box="[265,340,188,212]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/c7yt-hh77" name="Naturhistorisches Museum, Wien" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">NMW</collectionCode>
) made by Schedl from the 
<typeStatus box="[655,757,188,213]" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">holotype</typeStatus>
. The specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1009,1109,188,213]" name="Thailand" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(see below) agree with both Beeson’s description and the drawing. The species is clearly related to 
<taxonomicName box="[962,1133,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lewisi">
<emphasis box="[962,1133,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Platypus lewisi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1191,1356,223,248]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Carchesiopygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobacanthus">
<emphasis box="[1191,1356,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">P. lobacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It has the characters of 
<taxonomicName box="[343,441,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[343,441,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Platypus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, not 
<taxonomicName box="[498,677,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Carchesiopygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,677,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">Carchesiopygus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is here transferred to 
<emphasis box="[976,1082,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="411">
<taxonomicName box="[976,1078,260,285]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Platypus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="411" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Platypus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
